The paper deals with declarative networking, which is a subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper proposes a declarative, model-based semantics for Datalog-like languages, which falls under the category of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the challenges of concurrency and asynchronous communication, which are relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and networked systems (cs.NI).
